A space for a Jupyter notebook image on the left, and on the right the following bullet points:
* Use the total flux per second from each pixel to predict the flux in each image in the stack
* Create a difference image between the predicted and real data
* Rice encode the resulting difference images
* Compression ratios of 3-5x for all the images (at the price of one additional "rate" image)

